'''Alexis Jesse M. Saelemaekers'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.legaseriea.it/uploads/default/attachments/comunicati/comunicati_m/8393/files/allegati/8489/cu267.pdf |title=Comunicato Ufficiale N. 267 |trans-title=Official Communication No. 267 |publisher=[[Lega Serie A]] |page=3 |date=19 July 2020 |access-date=15 November 2022 |language=it |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200720230557/https://www.legaseriea.it/uploads/default/attachments/comunicati/comunicati_m/8393/files/allegati/8489/cu267.pdf |archive-date=20 July 2020}}</ref> (born 27 June 1999) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|wing-back]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

==Club career==
===Anderlecht===
{{BLP unreferenced section|date=July 2024}}
In October 2017, Saelemaekers signed a contract at [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] until 2019. On 16 February 2018, he made his official debut against [[Sint-Truidense VV|Sint-Truiden]]. He came on as a substitute in the 77th minute. On 8 June 2018, Saelemaekers renewed his contract until 2022.

===AC Milan===
On 31 January 2020, [[AC Milan]] signed Saelemaekers on loan, with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2020-01-31/saelemaekers-is-a-new-ac-milan-player |title=Saelemaekers is a new AC Milan player|website=AC Milan |date=31 January 2020|access-date=4 July 2020}}</ref> Milan reportedly agreed a €3.5 million fee plus €1 million in bonuses in case of a permanent signing.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/149456/milan-make-saelemaekers-signing |title=Milan make Saelemaekers signing|website=Football Italia |date=1 February 2020 |access-date=4 July 2020}}</ref> The same year on 2 February, he made his league debut as a substitute to [[Davide Calabria]] in a 1–1 draw against [[Hellas Verona|Verona]] on 2 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news|first=Monica|last=Colombo|title=Milan-Verona 1-1: senza Ibrahimovic i rossoneri frenano. L'esordio di Daniel Maldini|url=https://www.corriere.it/sport/20_febbraio_02/milan-verona-1-1-senza-ibrahimovic-rossoneri-frenano-l-esordio-daniel-maldini-b19bd574-45cd-11ea-89f5-524fb04840d5.shtml?refresh_ce-cp|newspaper=[[Corriere Della Sera]]|date=3 February 2020|language=it}}</ref>

On 1 July 2020, Saelemaekers signed a contract with Milan which would keep him at the club until 30 June 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Comunicato Ufficiale: Alexia Saelemaekers|url=https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/articoli/media/2020-07-01/comunicato-ufficiale-alexis-saelemaekers|website=AC Milan|access-date=1 July 2020}}</ref> On 18 July, he scored his first goal for the club in a 5–1 home win over [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] in Serie A.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/serie-a/2020-07-18/bologna-put-to-the-sword-at-san-siro |title=Match report AC Milan 5-1 Bologna, Serie A 2019/2020|publisher=AC Milan |date=18 July 2020 |access-date=19 July 2020 |archive-date=22 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222112141/https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/serie-a/2020-07-18/bologna-put-to-the-sword-at-san-siro |url-status=live}}</ref>

In October 2020, Saelemaekers scored his first goal of the season against [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] in qualification match for Europa league.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Rio Ave 2-2 AC Milan|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54381408|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|access-date=11 March 2022}}</ref> His next goal came on 26 October against Roma in 3–3 draw,<ref>{{Cite news|title=AC Milan 3-3 Roma|work=BBC Sport |date=26 October 2020 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54700224|access-date=11 March 2022}}</ref> his third and last goal of the season was on 20 December against Sassuolo as Milan pulled an away 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rafael Leão scores quickest ever Serie A goal to spark AC Milan victory|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/sassuolo-vs-milan/cronica/2020/12/20/5fdf7b4be2704ecb888b45f9.html|website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|date=20 December 2020 |access-date=11 March 2022}}</ref> In total, he scored three goals and five [[Assist (association football)|assists]] of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Alexis Saelemaekers|url=https://en.as.com/resultados/ficha/deportista/alexis_saelemaekers/43547/2020/estadisticas/|website=[[Diario AS]]|access-date=11 March 2022}}</ref>

On 15 October 2021, Saelemaekers extended his contract until 30 June 2026 with a raise in salary.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Alexis Saelemaekers rinnova il contratto con l'AC Milan: Il comunicato ufficiale|url=https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/articoli/media/2021-10-15/comunicato-ufficiale-alexis-saelemaekers|website=AC Milan|language=it}}</ref> On 4 December, he scored his first goal of this season against [[US Salernitana 1919|Salernitana]], a powerful left footed shot in eventual 2–0 win.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Oliver|last=Fisher|title=AC Milan 2-0 Salernitana|url=https://sempremilan.com/match-report-ac-milan-salernitana|website=Smpre Milan|date=4 December 2021 |access-date=11 March 2022}}</ref> His next goal came in a [[Coppa Italia]] match against [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]] on 13 January 2022, a goal in extra time as Milan won 3–1.<ref>{{Cite news|title=AC Milan 3-1 Genoa|work=BBC Sport |date=13 January 2022 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/59988102|access-date=11 March 2022}}</ref>

====Loan to Bologna====
On 30 August 2023, Saelemaekers joined [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] on loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Alexis Saelemaekers joins Bologna|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/en/alexis-saelemaekers-joins-bologna/|website=Bologna FC 1900|date=30 August 2023|access-date=30 August 2023}}</ref> At Bologna, Saelemaekers quickly established himself as an important player, fitting perfectly into the manager [[Thiago Motta]]'s so-called 2–7–2 system.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Calum|last=Ritchie|title=Thiago Motta's "Super Offensive" 2-7-2 Formation Explained|url=https://www.givemesport.com/thiago-mottas-2-7-2-formation-explained/|website=Give Me Sport|date=13 June 2024}}</ref> Due to the presence of [[Riccardo Orsolini]] on the right side as an "inverted" left-footed right winger, right-footed Saelemaekers began to play on the left in the similar role, a position he sometimes played in at Milan in absence of regular starter [[Rafael Leão]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Oliver|last=Fisher|title=GdS: Probable XI for AC Milan vs. Inter {{!}} Saelemaekers on the left wing|url=https://sempremilan.com/gds-probable-xis-ac-milan-inter-champions|website=Sempre Milan|date=9 May 2023|access-date=11 July 2024}}</ref> Saelemaekers was about to join Bologna on a full transfer from Milan before [[Vincenzo Italiano]] took over the departing Thiago Motta as a manager at the end of the season and declined to spend €10 million on the player, focusing on other transfer targets.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Oliver|last=Fisher|title=GdS: Bologna will not use €9.5m Saelemaekers option {{!}} He will return to Milan|url=https://sempremilan.com/gds-bologna-9-5m-saelemaekers-milan-return|website=Sempre Milan|date=6 June 2024}}</ref>

While initially on the summer transfer market due to oversaturation of attacking players on both wings, Saelemaekers returned to AC Milan's training camp in July, played in all the pre-season friendlies, and was even a surprise starter for the opening 2024–25 Serie A game versus [[Torino FC|Torino]], playing as a [[left back]] in place of [[Theo Hernandez]], who later came on in the second half for [[Davide Calabria]], with Saelemaekers moving onto the right side of a back-four.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://milanreports.com/2024/08/17/ac-milan-left-back-saelemaekers | title=AC Milan - Torino &#124; Official lineups - Saelemaekers starts as a left-back | date=17 August 2024 }}</ref>

====Loan to Roma====
On 30 August 2024, he joined fellow Serie A club [[AS Roma|Roma]], on loan for the [[2024–25 AS Roma season|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.asroma.com/en/news/71767/alexis-saelemaekers-signs-for-roma |title=Alexis Saelemaekers signs for Roma|publisher=[[AS Roma|Roma]]|date=30 August 2024|accessdate=30 August 2024}}</ref> He scored a career high 7 goals in all competitions before returning to Milan at the end of the season.

==International career==
Saelemaekers debuted with the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]] in a 1–1 [[Exhibition match#Association football|friendly]] draw with [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]] on 8 October 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Pierre|last=Lambert|title=Alexis Saelemaekers "ne pouvait pas rêver mieux" pour ses débuts|trans-title=Alexis Saelemaekers couldn't ask for a better result for his debut|url=https://www.rtbf.be/article/alexis-saelemaekers-ne-pouvait-pas-rever-mieux-pour-ses-debuts-10604347|website=[[RTBF]]|date=8 October 2020|access-date=11 July 2024|language=fr}}</ref> In September 2021, he scored his first goal in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Saelemaekers na sterke prestaties: "Ik zal de keuzes van Martinez respecteren"|url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/996769/saelemaekers-na-sterke-prestaties-ik-zal-de-keuzes-van-martinez-respecteren.html|website=Voetbal Primeur|date=9 September 2021|access-date=11 July 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

